42:03.800 --> 42:07.600
And that's something that is positive for the future.

42:07.600 --> 42:11.280
But you also need to get prepared because it changes a lot of things.

42:11.280 --> 42:14.320
The architecture of running AI is complicated.

42:14.320 --> 42:17.840
It's much more harder to run it on premise.

42:17.840 --> 42:21.480
And so you need to find solutions for that.

42:21.480 --> 42:23.920
We're working on AI at Xwiki.

42:23.920 --> 42:25.400
We have an extension.

42:25.400 --> 42:32.240
And we also gained a research project to do some search engine using AI.

42:32.240 --> 42:38.800
And I would like to point out the approach of also NextCloud with ethical AI.

42:38.800 --> 42:41.160
We are completely aligned with that aspect.

42:41.160 --> 42:46.040
You cannot do AI today without thinking about whether it's ethical,

42:46.040 --> 42:48.120
whether it's protecting data or not.

42:50.120 --> 42:56.440
One big aspect that I think is really important for the future is software modularity and integrations.

42:56.440 --> 43:05.560
We believe at Xwiki that the future of open source software is allowing to assemble software together.

43:05.560 --> 43:07.320
And making better reuse.

43:07.320 --> 43:12.280
I said at the beginning of Xwiki that when we started, we reused a lot of open source software.

43:12.280 --> 43:17.680
Well, if we want our software to survive in the open source world,

43:17.680 --> 43:20.680
we also need to make sure that it can be reused more.

43:20.680 --> 43:22.720
And this is why we've launched a new product.

43:22.720 --> 43:24.920
We call it Xwiki Crystal.

43:24.920 --> 43:29.160
And it's going to be a new modular AI that will not only work with Xwiki,

43:29.160 --> 43:33.760
but can work with other Wikis and can be integrated in other tools.

43:33.760 --> 43:36.840
And the other thing is that we're part of the Open Desk project,

43:36.840 --> 43:42.440
which is a funded project in Germany to make an open source suite of collaborative products.

43:42.440 --> 43:45.240
And we're very happy to be part of it.

43:45.240 --> 43:49.800
And the other aspect is doing with CripPad what we did with Xwiki.

43:49.800 --> 43:54.960
I showed the financial of Xwiki, the company that included both Xwiki and CripPad.

43:54.960 --> 43:58.880
